August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Human Voice\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|6|20|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = Norma Renault stars in the adaptation of a Jean Cocteau work<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=o44tAAAAIBAJ&pg=5491%2C3727053 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=20 June 1961 | page=17 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = A Day in the Life of the Great Scholar Wu\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|6|27|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = [[Bertolt Brecht]]\n| ShortSummary    = [[Ted Follows]] stars in this adaptation of a Brecht work.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=qY4tAAAAIBAJ&pg=5604%2C5044402| title=Today's TV Previews | date=27 June 1961 | page=12 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n|}\n\nThe initial 1961 half-season was pre-empted by extended hour-long editions of ''Close-Up'' on 31 January, 7 March, 25 April.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=FVUlAAAAIBAJ&&pg=5512%2C1461882 | title=Televiews | first=Andrew | last=Webster | date=7 March 1961 | page=17 | newspaper=Ottawa Citizen | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=_Y4tAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Hp0FAAAAIBAJ&pg=6870%2C4859438 | title=Dial Turns | first=Bernard | last=Dube | page=13 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=25 April 1961 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref> [[Stanley Cup]] playoff broadcasts also pre-empted ''Q for Quest'' on 21 March and 4 April 1961. The 2 May episode was pre-empted by the special documentary ''University''.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=tY0tAAAAIBAJ&pg=5710%2C278196 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=2 May 1961 | page=9 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n\n===Season 2: 1961\u20131962===\nThe first full season of ''Quest'' aired on Sundays at 10:30&nbsp;p.m. (Eastern).\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto;\"\n|-\n! Title\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Writer\n! style=\"width:10em;\" | Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Asylum\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|10|8|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = [[Pierre Gascar]]\n| ShortSummary    = This drama concerns Rose Schmidt (Elise Charette) who is committed to a psychiatric hospital. Producer Harvey Hart adapted Gascar's play for this episode. [[Victoria Mitchell (actor)|Victoria Mitchell]] and [[Catherine Proctor]] also star.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=SI4tAAAAIBAJ&pg=4039%2C1260550 | title=Montreal Actress To Star In The Asylum on Quest | date=7 October 1961 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | page=22 | accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Alcoholic Veteran with the Washboard Cranium\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|10|15|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = Henry Miller\n| ShortSummary    = <ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=To4tAAAAIBAJ&pg=2225%2C2545879 | title=Weekend TV Previews | date=14 October 1961 | page=22 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Jackie and Roy in Love\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|10|22|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = Jackie Cain and Roy Kral are a married singing duo who perform songs about courtship.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=bSAyAAAAIBAJ&pg=4773%2C1268006 | title=Sunday highlights | page=TV4 | newspaper=Ottawa Citizen | date=21 October 1961 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=Fr8DH2VBP9sC&dat=19611021&printsec=frontpage&hl=en | title=Weekend TV Previews | date=21 October 1961 | pa