itle           = Paul Loves Libby\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|2|17|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = Philip Roth\n| ShortSummary    = Graydon Gould, Cec Linder, Martha Henry, Larry D. Mann star in this play based on Roth's novel ''[[Letting Go (novel)|Letting Go]]''.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-I4jAAAAIBAJ&pg=5177%2C2908989 | title=Weekend TV Previews | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=16 February 1963 | page=10 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Oppenheimer\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|2|24|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = Alan King\n| ShortSummary    = This docudrama concerns the 1954 security hearings of [[J. Robert Oppenheimer]] whose suspension from the Atomic Energy Commission included allegations that he improperly associated with communists. Fletcher Markle portrays Oppenheimer; other cast members in this George McCowan production include John Bethune, Ed McNamara, Ruth Springford and Alexander Webster.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=_Y4jAAAAIBAJ&pg=7302%2C4235214 | title=Oppenheimer's Hearing Recreated on Quest | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=23 February 1963 | page=13 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Wounded Soldier\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|3|3|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = George Garrett\n| ShortSummary    = Jack Kuper adapted Garrett's short story concerning a soldier who seeks to avoid isolation from society. Mario Prizek produced and directed.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=IKUtAAAAIBAJ&pg=5469%2C307411 | title=Weekend TV Previews | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=2 March 1963 | page=22 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref><ref name=Contrast308 />\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Gallows Humor (part 1)\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|3|17|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = Jack Richardson\n| S