3 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=7 February 1961 | page=9 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = For The Information of Husbands\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|2|14|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = [[Anton Chekov]]\n| ShortSummary    = [[Frances Hyland]] and [[Larry D. Mann]] star in this performance of Chekov's story. Adaptation by [[Mac Shoub]], Leo Orenstein producer.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=7JQtAAAAIBAJ&pg=7154%2C2435291 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=14 February 1961 | page=11 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Blues\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|2|21|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = A conversation concerning blues music with [[Ed Bickert]], [[Don Francks]], [[Eve Smith]], the Don Thompson Quintet; [[Daryl Duke]] producer.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=8pQtAAAAIBAJ&pg=5558%2C3828794 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=21 February 1961 | page=13 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Return Journey\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|2|28|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = [[Douglas Rain]] and Diana Maddox perform an autobiographical play about Dylan Thomas; Paul Almond producer.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-JQtAAAAIBAJ&pg=7091%2C5110202 | title=Today's TV Previews | date=28 February 1961 | page=10 | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Bikel Calling\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1961|3|14|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = A feature on performer [[Theodore Bikel]], produced by Stan Harris.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspape