11 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = Night of Admission\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|11|19|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = Frank Freedman\n| ShortSummary    = Dramatic play set in a hospital, starring Don Francks and Joe Austen.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=6jgjAAAAIBAJ&pg=7193%2C3934011 | title=Today's TV Previews | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=19 November 1963 | page=11 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/film-video-sound-database/Pages/item.aspx?IdNumber=290189 | title=Night of Admission (290189) | publisher=Library and Archives Canada | accessdate=20 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The World of Kurt Weill in Song, part 1\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|11|26|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = Musical episode starring Martha Schlamme and Will Holt performing portions of their New York revue of Kurt Weill's music. Harvey Hart produced this broadcast which was recorded in Toronto at [[Casa Loma]]'s Dungeonette Room.<ref name=\"Today's TV Previews\">{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=A5otAAAAIBAJ&pg=5111%2C332648 | title=Today's TV Previews | newspaper=The Gazette | location=Montreal | date=3 December 1963 | page=19 | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://newspaperarchive.com/winnipeg-free-press-nov-02-1963-p-76/ | title=Casa Loma Setting | date=2 November 1963 | newspaper=Winnipeg Free Press | accessdate=21 August 2017 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The World of Kurt Weill in Song, part 2\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1963|12|3|df=y}}\n| WrittenBy       = \u2013\n| ShortSummary    = The concluding part of this musical performance starring Martha Schlamme and Will Holt.<ref name=\"Today's TV Previews\">{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspape