mn Magon]]}}\n}}\n| developer                = {{Plainlist|\n* Matt Youngberg\n* Francisco Angones<ref name=\"CBRCarlBarks\" />\n}}\n| voices                   = {{plainlist|\n* [[David Tennant]]\n* [[Danny Pudi]]\n* [[Ben Schwartz]]\n* [[Bobby Moynihan]]\n* [[Kate Micucci]]\n* [[Beck Bennett]]\n* [[Toks Olagundoye]]\n* [[Tony Anselmo]]\n* [[Paget Brewster]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Mark Mueller]]\n| opentheme                = \"DuckTales\"<br/> by [[Felicia Barton]]\n| endtheme                 = \"DuckTales\" (Instrumental)\n| composer                 = [[Dominic Lewis]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 3 <!-- season the last aired episode belongs to -->\n| num_episodes             = 51 <!-- only increment when new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes            = List of DuckTales (2017 TV series) episodes\n| executive_producer       = Matt Youngberg<br>Francisco Angones {{small|(co-executive producer, season 3\u2013present)}}\n| producer                 = <!-- usually gets the produced by credit in an episode -->Suzanna Olson<br>Fracisco Angones {{small|(co-producer, seasons 1 and 2)}}\n| editor                   = {{plainlist|\n*Jasmine Bocz\n*Jon Price\n}}\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes<br />44 minutes {{small|(special episodes only)}}\n| company                  = [[Disney Television Animation]]\n| distributor              = <!-- needs a reference -->\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2017|8|12}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = https://disneynow.go.com/shows/ducktales-disney-channel\n| image_alt                = Titlecard, featuring the show's protagonists and Launchpad's crashed airplane.\n| channel                  = [[Disney XD]] <small>(2017, 2020\u2013present)</small><br />[[Disney Channel]] <small>(2018\u201319)</small>\n| related                  = ''[[DuckTales]]'' (original series)\n}}\n\n'''''DuckTales''''' is an American [[Animated series#Television|animated television series]], developed by Matt Youngberg and Francisco Angones originally just for [[Disney XD]], and then later for [[Disney Channel]] as well. Produced by [[Disney Television Animation]], the series is a [[Reboot (fiction)|reboot]] of the [[DuckTales|original 1987 series of the same name]]. ''DuckTales'' was officially announced in February 2015 and premiered on August 12, 2017 with a 44-minute special titled \"Woo-oo!\" The first season, which resumed on September 23, 2017, consisted of 21 further twenty-two minute episodes and a 44-minute season finale special.<ref name=\"ScreenRant\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadline.com/2017/06/ducktales-cartoon-reboot-premiere-date-disney-xd-1202113080/|title=\u2018DuckTales\u2019: Cartoon Reboot Gets Premiere Date On Disney XD|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=June 14, 2017|publisher=Deadline|accessdate=September 2, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170904215600/http://www.deadline.com/2017/06/ducktales-cartoon-reboot-premiere-date-disney-xd-1202113080/|archivedate=September 4, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Before the series was released, it was renewed for a second season on March 2, 2017.<ref name=Deadline030217/>\n\nThe second season premiered on October 20, 2018.<ref name=\"S2PremiereS3Renew\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ducktales-renewed-season-3-disney-channel-1145964|title='Ducktales' Renewed for Season 3 on Disney Channel Ahead of Season 2 Premiere|website=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Rick|last=Porter|date=September 21, 2018}}</ref> On September 21, 2018, it was announced that ''DuckTales'' was renewed for a third season,<ref name=\"S2PremiereS3Renew\" /> which premiered on April 4, 2020.<ref name=\"Season3Premiere\">{{cite web |last1=Trumbore |first1=Dave |title=Disney\u2019s \u2018DuckTales\u2019 Season 3 to Arrive Early This April with Guest Stars Aplenty |url=https://collider.com/ducktales-season-3-release-date/ |website=Collider |accessdate=20 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n[[File:DuckTales 2017 Scrooge Donald Huey Dewey Louie.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Scrooge McDuck (right), Donald's nephews Huey (red), Dewey (blue), and Louie (green), and Donald Duck in the 2017 series.]]\nAfter not speaking to each other for ten years, [[Scrooge McDuck]] is reunited with his estranged nephew [[Donald Duck]] when he asks him to babysit his three nephews, [[Huey, Dewey, and Louie]], for the day. The boys\u2019 presence rekindles Scrooge's sense of [[adventure]], and he invites them and Donald to live at McDuck Manor with him, his housekeeper [[Mrs. Beakley]], and her granddaughter [[Webby Vanderquack]]. Together, they go on many new treasure-hunting expeditions and globe-trotting adventures while contending with villains like [[Flintheart Glomgold]], the [[Beagle Boys]], and Mark Beaks.\n\nIn season one, Dewey and Webby seek the truth behind Scrooge and Donald's strained relationship and the unexplained disappearance of the boys\u2019 mother and Donald's twin sister, [[Della Duck]], all while the sorceress [[Magica De Spell]] manipulates events to facilitate her return and get revenge on Scrooge.\n\nIn season two, Scrooge and Glomgold compete to make the most money within the year, with the ownership of both their companies at stake, while Louie tries to start up his own multi-million dollar business in hopes of following in Scrooge's footsteps. Della is also reunited with her family following her escape from the [[Moon]] and adapts to her newfound motherhood, unaware that Donald is being held prisoner there and the Moonlanders are planning to invade Earth.\n\nIn season three, the secret organization [[F.O.W.L.]] plot to eliminate the Duck Family following the Moonlander invasion. After Scrooge discovers a journal leading to several lost treasures that F.O.W.L.'s after, the two forces go on a race against time to claim them before the other one can.\n\n==Voice cast==\n{{Main|List of DuckTales characters}}\nThe show's main voice cast includes:<ref name=\"Futon Season One\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2017/06/14/disneys-new-ducktales-takes-flight-with-tv-movie-and-series-premiering-saturday-august-12-and-saturday-september-23-respectively-on-disney-xd-107011/20170614disneyxd01/|title=Disney's New \"DuckTales\" Takes Flight with TV Movie and Series Premiering Saturday, August 12, and Saturday, September 23, Respectively, on Disney XD|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=October 15, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Season3Premiere\" />\n\n* [[David Tennant]] as [[Scrooge McDuck]]\n* [[Danny Pudi]] as [[Huey, Dewey, and Louie|Huey Duck]]\n* [[Ben Schwartz]] as [[Huey, Dewey, and Louie|Dewey Duck]]\n* [[Bobby Moynihan]] as [[Huey, Dewey, and Louie|Louie Duck]]\n* [[Kate Micucci]] as [[Webby Vanderquack]]\n* [[Beck Bennett]] as [[Launchpad McQuack]]\n* [[Toks Olagundoye]] as [[Mrs. Beakley]]\n* [[Tony Anselmo]] as [[Donald Duck]]\n* [[Paget Brewster]] as [[Della Duck]]\n\n==Production==\nMatt Youngberg and Francisco Angones grew up watching the original series and had always wanted to develop an updated version for a newer generation. Youngberg said, \"We're hoping that in thirty years, the kids who watch our show will then be bringing back the next version of ''DuckTales'' because they loved what we did so much.\"<ref name=\"syfy\">{{cite web|url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/ducktales-creators-talk-gizmoduck-and-casting-lin-manuel-miranda|title=SDCC 2017: DuckTales Creators Talk Gizmoduck and Casting Lin-Manuel Miranda|last=Mason|first=Heather|website=Syfy Wire|date=July 22, 2017|accessdate=September 16, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170917075307/http://www.syfy.com/syfywire/ducktales-creators-talk-gizmoduck-and-casting-lin-manuel-miranda|archivedate=September 17, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2015, [[Terry McGovern (actor)|Terry McGovern]], the original voice of Launchpad McQuack, stated in an interview that the entire voice cast from the original series would not be returning for the reboot, which made him \"heartsick\" at the news.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ducktales Cast Not Returning for Reboot|url=http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/news/Ducktales-Cast-Not-Returning-for-Reboot/|website=Behind the Voice Actors|publisher=OptimusSolo|accessdate=19 May 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526071332/http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/news/Ducktales-Cast-Not-Returning-for-Reboot/|archivedate=May 26, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The new voice cast for the series was revealed on December 16, 2016 in a video where they sing an [[a cappella]] version of the original theme song in promotion of the news.<ref name=Deadline121616/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/06/08/ducktales-exclusive-characters-cast/|title='DuckTales' Exclusive: Meet the New Faces of Duckburg|date=June 8, 2017|publisher=|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170611100329/http://ew.com/tv/2017/06/08/ducktales-exclusive-characters-cast/|archivedate=June 11, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/herocomplex/la-et-hc-ducktales-premiere-date-opening-title-20170614-story.html|title=Watch the new 'DuckTales' opening title sequence, woo-ooo!|first=Tracy|last=A52A2A|date=June 14, 2017|publisher=|via=LA Times|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170621185210/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/herocomplex/la-et-hc-ducktales-premiere-date-opening-title-20170614-story.html|archivedate=June 21, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The following May, [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]] was announced as the voice of [[Gizmoduck|Fenton Crackshell-Cabrera / Gizmoduck]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|title=Lin Manuel-Miranda Joins Voice Cast as Fenton Crackshell /Gizmoduck|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/ducktales-lin-manuel-miranda-joins-voice-cast-disney-xd-1202097756/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 19, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20171025204408/http://deadline.com/2017/05/ducktales-lin-manuel-miranda-joins-voice-cast-disney-xd-1202097756/|archivedate=October 25, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The character was changed to being Latino due to Lin-Manuel's heritage and because Angones felt that there were not enough positive Latino superheroes.<ref name=\"syfy\" /> In June, more cast members, including [[Tony Anselmo]] reprising his role as [[Donald Duck]], were announced,<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Marc|last=Snetiker|title=DuckTales Exclusive: Characters Cast|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/06/08/ducktales-exclusive-characters-cast/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City|date=June 8, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170611100329/http://ew.com/tv/2017/06/08/ducktales-exclusive-characters-cast/|archivedate=June 11, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and during the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]], Disney announced that [[Darkwing Duck (character)|Darkwing Duck]] would also make an appearance in the TV series.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/07/21/darkwing-duck-ducktales-revival/|title=Darkwing Duck is headed to DuckTales revival|first=Marc|last=Snetiker|date=July 21, 2017|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722093515/http://ew.com/tv/2017/07/21/darkwing-duck-ducktales-revival/|archivedate=July 22, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2019 San Diego Comic-Con, several characters from other [[Disney Television Animation]] cartoons were revealed to appear in the show's third season; the Rescue Rangers from ''[[Chip 'n Dale: Rescue Rangers]]''; Kit Cloudkicker and Molly Cunningham from ''[[TaleSpin]]''; Rhinokey and Butterbear from ''[[The Wuzzles]]'', and Gosalyn Mallard and Taurus Bulba from ''Darkwing Duck'', as well as classic Disney characters [[Chip 'n Dale]] (based on their ''Rescue Rangers'' incarnations), [[Goofy]] (based on his ''[[Goof Troop]]'' incarnation) and [[Daisy Duck]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/comic-con/2019/07/19/ducktales-rescue-rangers-talespin/|title=DuckTales surprises Comic-Con with Rescue Rangers, Daisy Duck, and Lin-Manuel Miranda|first=Marc|last=Snetiker|date=July 20, 2019|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City}}</ref>\n\nThe art style of the show is heavily influenced not just by [[Carl Barks]]' original ''[[Uncle Scrooge]]'' comics, but also some of Barks' paintings.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.facebook.com/DisneyXD/videos/1656336367741121 |title=XD video about DuckTales art style |author= Disney XD |publisher= Facebook |date=August 12, 2017 |accessdate= August 14, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"CBRCarlBarks\">{{cite web |url= http://www.cbr.com/ducktales-comics-inspired-cartoon-classic/ |title= DuckTales: The Disney Comics That Inspired The Cartoon Classic |last= Speelman |first=Tom |website= [[Comic Book Resources]] |publisher=Valnet, Inc.|location=Montreal, Quebec, Canada|date=August 12, 2017 |access-date= August 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl= http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170816003612/http://www.cbr.com/ducktales-comics-inspired-cartoon-classic |archivedate= August 16, 2017 |df=mdy-all}}</ref> The theme song, written by [[Mark Mueller]] for the 1987 series, was re-recorded for the 2017 reboot.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ducktales-theme-song-gets-an-update-disney-xd-reboot-1013219|title='DuckTales' Theme Song Gets an Update for Disney XD Reboot |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |date= June 14, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Valence Media]]|location=Los Angeles, California|accessdate= June 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl= http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170614160328/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ducktales-theme-song-gets-an-update-disney-xd-reboot-1013219|archivedate=June 14, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It was arranged by Michael \"Smidi\" Smithand and TJ Stafford and sung by [[Felicia Barton]].<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Darryn|last=King|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/08/the-story-of-the-ducktales-theme-music|title=The Story of the DuckTales Theme, History's Catchiest Single Minute of Music|magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|location=New York City|date=August 9, 2017|access-date=November 6, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910004242/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/08/the-story-of-the-ducktales-theme-music|archivedate=September 10, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nDonald Duck has a larger role in this version compared to the 1980s version. The earlier version had been restricted by an edict from [[The Walt Disney Company]] stating that the television studio could not use Donald or any of the other stars from Disney's Golden Age shorts, only allowing Donald to make short cameos to set up storylines;<ref name=fbee>{{cite news|last1=Bentley|first1=Rick|title=Disney TV Animation Is 30 Years Old, and It's Going Strong|url=http://www.vnews.com/news/nation/world/14417461-95/disney-tv-animation-is-30-years-old-and-its-going-strong|accessdate=April 21, 2015|work=[[Valley News]]|agency=[[The Fresno Bee]]|publisher=[[McClatchy]]|location=Fresno, California|date=November 19, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304093955/http://www.vnews.com/news/nation/world/14417461-95/disney-tv-animation-is-30-years-old-and-its-going-strong|archivedate=March 4, 2016}}</ref> this restriction was lifted shortly after the original version of ''DuckTales'' ended.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of DuckTales (2017 TV series) episodes}}\n{{:List of DuckTales (2017 TV series) episodes}}\n\n==Release==\n===Broadcast===\nThe 44 minute pilot, titled ''Woo-oo!'', premiered on August 12 at 12:00 AM and was repeated consecutively for the next 24 hours. Two days later on August 14, the pilot was also released on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gP0Neif7Y4E|title=Woo-oo! (Full Episode) &#124; DuckTales &#124; Disney XD|date=August 14, 2017|website=YouTube|accessdate=September 11, 2017|publisher=Disney XD|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815002635/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gP0Neif7Y4E|archivedate=August 15, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The pilot also aired on [[Disney Channel]] on September 17, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Disney Channel Listings|url=http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tvlistings/ZCSGrid.do?stnNum=10171|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170918175943/http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tvlistings/ZCSGrid.do?stnNum=10171|archivedate=September 18, 2017|date=September 18, 2017}}</ref> The series officially premiered on September 23, 2017, coinciding with the original show's 30th anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/860854/ducktales-reboot-finally-has-a-premiere-date-hear-the-all-new-opening-theme-song|title=The DuckTales Reboot Finally Has a Premiere Date|publisher=|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614210807/http://www.eonline.com/news/860854/ducktales-reboot-finally-has-a-premiere-date-hear-the-all-new-opening-theme-song|archivedate=June 14, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On May 1, 2018, the show moved to the [[Disney Channel]], with new episodes airing on Fridays beginning May 4, 2018.{{cn|date=March 2020}} With season three, the series will once again air on Disney XD.<ref name=\"S3Premiere\" />{{deadlink|date=March 2020}}<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JxiAhXJewhw Season 3 is Coming! | DuckTales | Disney XD]</ref>\n\nIn Canada, the pilot premiered on [[Disney XD (Canada)|Disney XD]] on August 12 and the full series started on September 23, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI1YwYrHt3o|title=Disney XD Canada: Ducktales (2017) Promo #2 (2017)|last=Vo|first=Ryan|work=YouTube|date=July 12, 2017|accessdate=November 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506210347/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI1YwYrHt3o|archivedate=May 6, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/disneyxdcanada/videos/1117226048412360/?permPage=1|title=You know him, you love him...it's Donald Duck!|date=September 21, 2017|work=Facebook|author=Disney XD Canada|accessdate=November 30, 2017}}</ref> In Australia and New Zealand, the show premiered on [[Disney Channel (Australia and New Zealand)|Disney Channel]] on October 13, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://disneychannel.disney.com.au/ducktales/join-quackiest-family-new-adventure/|title=JOIN THE QUACKIEST FAMILY ON A NEW ADVENTURE!|work=Disney Channel Australia & New Zealand|accessdate=November 30, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201035015/https://disneychannel.disney.com.au/ducktales/join-quackiest-family-new-adventure/|archivedate=December 1, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In the United Kingdom and Ireland, the pilot premiered on [[Disney Channel (UK & Ireland)|Disney Channel]] on November 4, 2017. The full series debuted on March 1, 2018 on [[Disney XD (United Kingdom and Ireland)|Disney XD]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tv.bt.com/tv/tv-from-bt/ducktales-is-back-on-disney-channel-woo-oo-when-is-it-on-tv-in-the-uk-who-are-the-voice-cast-all-you-need-to-know-about-scrooge-mcducks-return-11364221011312|title=DuckTales is back on Disney Channel - Woo-oo!|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|date=October 16, 2017|work=BT|accessdate=November 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201041919/http://tv.bt.com/tv/tv-from-bt/ducktales-is-back-on-disney-channel-woo-oo-when-is-it-on-tv-in-the-uk-who-are-the-voice-cast-all-you-need-to-know-about-scrooge-mcducks-return-11364221011312|archivedate=December 1, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nOn December 7, 2016, a teaser trailer was released for the series. The first season was announced to consist of 21 half-hour episodes and two hour-long specials. On March 10, 2017, a trailer for the series aired on Disney Channel during the premiere of ''[[Tangled: Before Ever After]]'', and on June 14, 2017, the title sequence for the series, featuring a re-recording of the theme song written by [[Mark Mueller]] and performed by [[Felicia Barton]], was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2017/06/14/ducktales-premiere-date-reboot-theme-song/|title=Here's how 'DuckTales' reimagined that iconic theme song for Disney's reboot|first=Laura|last=Prudom|website=Mashable|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170707213501/http://mashable.com/2017/06/14/ducktales-premiere-date-reboot-theme-song/|archivedate=July 7, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nA DVD titled ''Woo-oo!'' was released on December 19, 2017 in the US<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/releases/DuckTales-Volume-Release/17766|title=DuckTales - Vol 1: Woo-Oo!|publisher=TV Shows on DVD|language=English|date=December 19, 2017|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205000855/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/releases/DuckTales-Volume-Release/17766|archivedate=February 5, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and on July 9, 2018 in the UK and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Duck-Tales-Woo-Oo-DVD/dp/B07CQL327S|title=Duck Tales: Woo-Oo! [DVD] [2018]|website=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> The DVD contains the pilot episode and all 6 ''Welcome to Duckburg'' shorts. A second DVD titled ''Destination Adventure!'' was released on June 5, 2018. It contains the episodes ''The Beagle Birthday Massacre!'', ''The Living Mummies of Toth-Ra!'', ''The Impossible Summit of Mt. Neverrest!'', ''The Spear of Selene!'', ''The Missing Links of Moorshire!'', and ''Beware the B.U.D.D.Y. System!'', as well as 2 episodes of the original 1987 series previously unreleased on DVD (''New Gizmo Kids on the Block'' and ''Ducky Mountain High'').<ref>{{cite web |last1=Celestino |first1=Mike |title=REVIEW: \"DuckTales \u2013 Destination: Adventure!\" DVD collects new and classic episodes of beloved Disney series |url=https://insidethemagic.net/2018/06/review-ducktales-destination-adventure-dvd-collects-new-and-classic-episodes-of-beloved-disney-series/ |website=Inside the Magic |accessdate=9 June 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%; margin: auto; text-align: center\"\n|+ DVD releases\n|-\n! Region\n! Set title\n! Seasons\n! Aspect ratio\n! Episode count\n! Release date\n|-\n| [[DVD region code|1]] & 2\n|Woo-oo!\n| \"align=\"center\" rowspan=\"2\"|1\n|1.78:1\n|align=center|1\n|December 19, 2017 <small>(Region 1)</small><br>July 9, 2018 <small>(Region 2)</small>\n|-\n| 1\n|Destination Adventure!\n|1.78:1, 1.33:1 (classic series)\n|align=center|6\n|June 5, 2018\n|}\n\n=== Video on demand ===\niTunes and Amazon Prime Video in the United States currently offer the first and second season, split into four volumes at $14.99 in SD format and $19.99 in HD format per volume.<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=zIgCyj6S5MY</ref> \n\nThe first and second season has been available on [[Disney+]]<ref>https://r.search.yahoo.com/_ylt=AwrP4o77TDBeGDkAzSsM34lQ;_ylu=X3oDMTByMWk2OWNtBGNvbG8DaXIyBHBvcwMyBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzcg--/RV=2/RE=1580252540/RO=10/RU=https%3a%2f%2fwww.disneyplus.com%2fseries%2fdisneys-ducktales-1987%2f1H1pGQ8RYFqN/RK=2/RS=KfNGNk8k3ezJG7SCNXTp6bswscM-</ref> since its launch (on 12 November 2019), but users have noted episodes being out of order.<ref>https://geekculture.co/disney-plus-is-missing-episodes-of-x-men-ducktales-and-the-simpsons-cartoons/</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports an approval rating of 100% based on 10 reviews, with an [[average rating]] of 9.0/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/ducktales/s01|title=DuckTales: Season 1 (2018)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202184559/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/ducktales/s01/|archivedate=December 2, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[IGN]]'s Chris Hayner gave the series premiere, \"Woo-oo!\", a score of 8.5 out of 10, stating that the reboot \"may be aimed at modern young audiences but there's no denying the heart and adventurous spirit it gets from the original series.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/09/ducktales-season-1-premiere-woo-oo-review|title=DuckTales: Season 1 Premiere \"Woo-oo!\" Review|first=Chris|last=Hayner|date=August 9, 2017|publisher=|accessdate=February 6, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20171005190541/http://www.ign.com/articles/2017/08/09/ducktales-season-1-premiere-woo-oo-review|archivedate=October 5, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the pilot episode was nominated for a [[Daytime Emmy Award]] in the Outstanding Special Class Animated Program category, but lost to ''[[A StoryBots Christmas]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://emmyonline.tv/daytime-emmy-awards/nominees/program-non-drama/|title=Daytime Emmys Nominees (Program - Non-Drama)|publisher=[[The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=April 23, 2019}}</ref> The following year saw the season one finale, \"The Shadow War\", nominated in the same category, but lost to ''[[Watership Down (miniseries)|Watership Down]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://emmyonline.tv/2019-daytime-emmy-awards/nominees-craft-non-drama-2019-daytime-emmy-awards/|title=Daytime Emmys Nominees (Craft - Non-Drama)|publisher=[[The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=May 8, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, ''DuckTales'' was also nominated for a Daytime Emmy in the Outstanding Casting for an Animated Series or Special category, but lost to fellow Disney series ''[[Elena of Avalor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://emmyonline.tv/nominees-childrens-animated-2019-daytime-emmy-awards/|title=Daytime Emmys Nominees (Children's / Animation)|publisher=[[The National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]|accessdate=May 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, at the Behind the Voice Actors Awards Ceremony, the cast was awarded the People's Choice Voice Acting Award in the Best Vocal Ensemble in a New Television Series category. Individual cast members David Tennant (Scrooge McDuck), Kate Micucci (Webby Vanderquack), Keith Ferguson (Flintheart Glomgold), Kimiko Glenn (Lena De Spell) and Margo Martindale (Ma Beagle) were all nominated, but none of the nominations resulted in any award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/btva-awards/2017/television/|title=7th Annual BTVA Voice Acting Award, 2017|publisher=Behind the Voice Actors|accessdate=April 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, the episode \"Who is Gizmoduck?\" was nominated for two [[Imagen Awards]].<ref>https://www.imagen.org/2019/07/01/nominations-announced-for-the-34th-annual-imagen-awards/</ref>\n\nDisney comics creator [[Don Rosa]], primarily known for his Uncle Scrooge comic sub-series ''[[The Life and Times of Scrooge McDuck]]'', has criticized the ''DuckTales'' reboot series, claiming that it bears \"virtually no resemblance whatsoever\" to Barks' original comics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/fourhman/status/911679205221466114?s=09|title=Don Rosa ain't messing aroundpic.twitter.com/ai4S1ZVC3f|first=Joe|last=Fourhman|date=September 23, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe series received controversy from the conservative group [[One Million Moms]] as the series introduced Violet's fathers who are the first LGBT characters in DuckTales.<ref>https://www.animationmagazine.net/events/lucky-13-miptv-2013-toon-highlights/</ref>\n\n==Printed media==\n===Prose books===\nIn 2018, [[Disney Press]] published \"DuckTales: Solving Mysteries and Rewriting History!\", a companion book covering the majority of season one, as seen from the perspective of Scrooge, Huey, Dewey, Louie, and Webby. It is written by [[Rob Renzetti]] and show writer Rachel Vine.<ref>{{cite book|title=DuckTales: Solving Mysteries and Rewriting History!|author=[[Rob Renzetti]] and Rachel Vine|url=https://books.disney.com/book/ducktales-solving-mysteries-and-rewriting-history/|accessdate=August 11, 2018|date=July 3, 2018|publisher=[[Disney Press]]|isbn=9781368008419}}</ref>\n\n===Comics===\nAn ongoing comic book series based on the show is being published by [[IDW Publishing]], with Joe Caramagna, [[Joey Cavalieri]] and Steve Behling sharing writing duties, and Luca Usai, Gianfranco Florio and others providing the art.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idwpublishing.com/ducktales-treasure-trove-graphic-novel-coming-from-idw/|title=\u2018DuckTales: Treasure Trove\u2019 Graphic Novel Coming From IDW|date=September 18, 2017|publisher=[[IDW Publishing]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023010655/http://www.idwpublishing.com/ducktales-treasure-trove-graphic-novel-coming-from-idw/|archivedate=October 23, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''Ducktales'' #0 was released on July 19, 2017, and #1 of the monthly series followed on September 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdist.com/disneys-ducktales-returns-to-comics-this-fall/|title=Disney\u2019s DUCKTALES Returns to Comics This Fall - Nerdist|date=June 16, 2017|publisher=|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616154941/http://nerdist.com/disneys-ducktales-returns-to-comics-this-fall/|archivedate=June 16, 2017|df=mdy-all|access-date=June 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe individual issues are also collected in [[Trade paperback (comics)|trade paperbacks]]:\n*\"Treasure Trove\" ({{isbn|9781684052080}}), collecting issues #0-2\n*\"Mysteries and Mallards\" ({{isbn|9781684052301}}), collecting issues #3-5\n*\"Quests and Quacks\" ({{isbn|9781684053193}}), collecting issues #6-8\n*\"Fowl Play\" ({{isbn|9781684054039}}), collecting issues #9-11\n*\"Monsters and Mayhem\" ({{isbn|9781684054909}}), collecting issues #12-14\n*\"Mischief and Miscreants\" ({{isbn|9781684055593}}), collecting issues #15-17\n*\"Imposters and Interns\"   ({{isbn|9781684056132}}), collecting issues #18-20\n\n'''List of comic book stories'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%; margin: auto; text-align: center\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:20%;\" scope=\"col\"|Story code\n! style=\"width:17%;\" scope=\"col\"|US publication\n! style=\"width:30%;\" scope=\"col\"|Title\n! style=\"width:15%;\" scope=\"col\"|Written by\n! style=\"width:18%;\" scope=\"col\"|Artist(s)\n! style=\"width:18%;\" scope=\"col\"| Short summary \n|-\n| XPW DTP CP 1-1<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inducks.org/story.php?c=XPW+DTP+CP+1-1|title=The Chilling Secret Of The Lighthouse! (XPW DTP CP 1-1) - I.N.D.U.C.K.S.|website=inducks.org}}</ref>\n| DuckTales #1\n| The Chilling Secret of the Lighthouse!\n| Joe Caramagna\n| Luca Usai\n| After Donald is hired to work in a lighthouse, Huey, Dewey and Louie decide to explore it.<ref name=\"comics.org\">https://www.comics.org/issue/1738357/</ref>\n|-\n| XPW DTP CP 1-2<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inducks.org/story.php?c=XPW+DTP+CP+1-2|title=The Repeating Revenge Of The Screaming Duck! (XPW DTP CP 1-2) - I.N.D.U.C.K.S.|website=inducks.org}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" | DuckTales #0\n| The Repeating Revenge of the Screaming Duck!\n| Joe Caramagna\n| Gianfranco Florio\n|  Huey, Dewey and Louie make a horror movie.<ref name=\"ReferenceF\">https://www.comics.org/issue/1722762/</ref>\n|-\n| XPW DTP CP 1-3<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inducks.org/story.php?c=XPW+DTP+CP+1-3|title=Big Trouble At Little Lake! (XPW DTP CP 1-3) - I.N.D.U.C.K.S.|website=inducks.org}}</ref>\n| Big Trouble at Little Lake!\n| Joe Caramagna\n| Andrea Greppi, <br />Paolo Campinoti, <br />Roberta Zanotta\n| Donald is stranded on an island with a tour group.<ref name=\"ReferenceF\"/> \n|-\n| XPW DTP CP 1-4<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inducks.org/story.php?c=XPW+DTP+CP+1-4|titl